All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Appointment
    creates Appointment objects and the getters, setters, formatting and comparison operations
    AppointmentCalendar
    holds and performs any operations on the appointments within the calendar for the application
    AppointmentEditController
    controller for 'AppointmentEditScreen.fxml' controls the appointment tables and the buttons to edit, delete appointments also controls the form for adding and editing appointments, including the save and clear buttons provides exit back to main appointment screen
    Contact
    creates Contact objects, minimizes getters and setters since application does not edit these also provides formatting and comparison operations
    ControllerUtilities
    contains the utilities used by one or more of the controllers to reduce repetitions.
    Country
    creates Country objects, formatting operations, with minimal getters or setters as application does not edit these
    Customer
    creates Customer objects and the getters, setters, and formatting operations
    CustomerController
    controller for 'Customer.fxml'
    CustomerList
    singleton class for creating, manipulating, and providing the customer list
    DbAppointments
    provides database access operations for the Appointment class
    DbConnection
    provides the methods for starting, getting and closing the connection to the MYSQL database
    DbContacts
    provides database access operations for the Contact class
    DbCustomers
    provides database access operations for the Customer class
    DbLocations
    provides database access operations for the Country and Division classes
    DbQuery
    provides functions for creating queries, getting result set, and setting and getting prepared statements
    DbUsers
    provides database access operations for the User class
    Division
    creates Division objects, including the getters, setters, and toString function
    LogInController
    controller for 'LogInScreen.fxml'
    Main
    main class starts the application and loads the log in screen
    MainAppointmentController
    controller for 'MainAppointment.fxml'
    ReportsController
    Controller for 'Reports.fxml'
    TimeZoneConversions
    provides time zone conversion methods to the application
    User
    creates user objects, manages list of users, user logged in, and basic functions to manage users minimizes getters and setters as this application is not used to manage user credentials
